19/02/2006
WASHINGTON, United States -- FBI chief Robert Mueller met with Bulgarian Interior Minister Rumen Petkov on Friday (17 February), urging concrete results in the fight against high-level corruption in Bulgaria. Petkov, wrapping up a several-day visit to the United States, said Mueller also called for continued improvements in bilateral co-operation.
In Sofia, meanwhile, US Ambassador John Beyrle met on Friday with Vassil Kirov, chief of the Bulgarian Agency for Financial Intelligence. Their talks focused on joint actions against money laundering and terrorism financing. (24 Chasa, Trud - 19/02/06) 
